ux standard, i.e. la recherche de solutions effectu=C3=A9e dans un espace r=
=C3=A9duit. L&#39;algorithme a =C3=A9t=C3=A9 impl=C3=A9ment=C3=A9 dans le p=
rototype, nomm=C3=A9 Star=C3=A9, et =C3=A9valu=C3=A9 avec diverses ontologi=
es. Deuxi=C3=A8mement, je me suis int=C3=A9ress=C3=A9 =C3=A0 augmenter le p=
ouvoir d&#39;expression de la logique de description en y rajoutant la ferm=
eture transitive de relations binaires qui s&#39;est montr=C3=A9e un connec=
teur logique int=C3=A9ressant pour la mod=C3=A9lisation des connaissances. =
A l&#39;aide de la m=C3=A9thode des tableaux compress=C3=A9s qui sert non s=
eulement =C3=A0 l&#39;optimisation mais aussi =C3=A0 la d=C3=A9termination =
de d=C3=A9cidabilit=C3=A9 d&#39;un langage, nous avons montr=C3=A9 qu&#39;u=
n nouveau langage r=C3=A9sultant d&#39;une combinaison libre d&#39;une logi=
que de description expressive avec la fermeture transitive est ind=C3=A9cid=
able. Ce r=C3=A9sultat nous a permis de proposer une restriction avec laque=
lle ce nouveau langage devient d=C3=A9cidable. Le troisi=C3=A8me aspect con=
cerne la r=C3=A9vision d&#39;une ontologie expressive. Lorsqu&#39;une nouve=
lle connaissance est ajout=C3=A9e =C3=A0 une ontologie, cette derni=C3=A8re=
 pourrait devenir incoh=C3=A9rente. Afin de restaurer la coh=C3=A9rence, il=
 est n=C3=A9cessaire de changer l&#39;ontologie initiale de telle fa=C3=A7o=
n que le changement soit minimal et la nouvelle connaissance soit prise en =
compte dans l&#39;ontologie r=C3=A9sultante. Nous avons propos=C3=A9 une m=
=C3=A9thode de r=C3=A9vision qui repose sur une caract=C3=A9risation de la =
s=C3=A9mantique d&#39;une ontologie en utilisant un ensemble fini de graphe=
s pour la repr=C3=A9sentation de mod=C3=A8les d&#39;ontologie. La m=C3=A9th=
ode a =C3=A9t=C3=A9 impl=C3=A9ment=C3=A9e dans le prototype mis en ligne, n=
omm=C3=A9 OntoRev.</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin:0px;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13px;line-height:norma=
l;font-family:Arial;color:rgb(26,26,26)"><span>Mots-cl=C3=A9s : Raisonnemen=
t, r=C3=A9vision, ontologie, logiques de description, m=C3=A9thode des tabl=
eaux</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin:0px;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13px;line-height:norma=
l;font-family:Arial;color:rgb(26,26,26);min-height:15px"><span></span><br><=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin:0px;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13px;line-height:norma=
l;font-family:Arial;color:rgb(26,26,26)"><span>Abstract : This habilitation=
 thesis outlines methods and tools resulting from my research activities du=
ring the last nine years. These methods and tools have been developed for r=
easoning and revision on knowledge bases used in the context of the Semanti=
c Web where data and knowledge stored in these bases would be represented i=
n a langage equipped with a formal and unambiguous semantics. Such a formal=
 semantics makes possible to develop an automated mechanism for reasoning o=
n the kind of such knowledge bases which are called ontologies in this thes=
is. In order to address the requirements for representing and exchanging da=
ta in the context of the Semantic Web, description logics (a decidable frag=
ment of First Order Logic) are used for &quot;encoding&quot; the semantics =
of the language OWL (Ontology Web Language) that was adopted by W3C. I was =
interested in developing algorithms and tools which allow for processing da=
ta and knowledge represented in description logics. My research therefore f=
ocuses on the three following topics. First, it is the development of an op=
timized tableau method, called compressed tableau, for reasoning on express=
ive ontologies. This method allows to obtain a worst-case optimal algorithm=
 in preserving the =C2=AB=C2=A0goal-oriented=C2=A0=C2=BB behavior of the st=
andard tableau method, i.e. searching performed in a reduced space. The met=
hod has been implemented in the prototype, named Star=C3=A9, and evaluated =
with various ontologies. Second, I was interested in augmenting the express=
ion power of description logics by adding the transitive closure of binary =
relations which is known as an interesting logical connector for knowledge =
modeling. By using the compressed tableau method which allows not only for =
optimization but also for determining decidability of a language, we have s=
howed that a new language obtained by fully combining an expressive descrip=
tion logic with the transitive closure may be undecidable. This result led =
us to propose a restriction which enables the new langage to be decidable. =
The third topic of my research is concerned with expressive ontology revisi=
on. When adding new knowledge to an ontology, it may become inconsistent. I=
n order to restore consistency of the ontology, it is needed to change the =
initial ontology in such a way that the change should be minimal and the ne=
w knowledge should be taken into account in the resulting ontology. We have=
 proposed a revision method which relies on a characterization of the seman=
tics of an ontology by using a finite set of graphs for representing ontolo=
gy models. The method has been implemented in the prototype available onlin=
e, named OntoRev. Keywords : Reasoning, revision, ontology, description log=
ics, tableau method</span></p><p style=3D"margin:0px;font-stretch:normal;fo=
nt-size:13px;line-height:normal;font-family:Arial;color:rgb(26,26,26)"><spa=
n><br></span></p><p style=3D"margin:0px;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13px;=
line-height:normal;font-family:Arial;color:rgb(26,26,26)"><span>Chan Le Duc=
